quran[15]{c,v,t,f}:
  37,91,"Then he turned to their gods and said, ",footnotes:1:[Consume the offerings placed before them.]
  37,92,"What is [wrong] with you that you do not speak?"
  37,93,"And he turned upon them a blow with [his] right hand."
  38,70,"It has not been revealed to me except that I am a clear warner."
  38,71,"[So mention] when your Lord said to the angels, "
  38,72,"So when I have proportioned him and breathed into him of My [created] soul,{1} then fall down to him in prostration.",footnotes:1:[See footnote to 15:29.]
  39,55,"And follow the best of what was revealed to you from your Lord [i.e., the Qur’ān] before the punishment comes upon you suddenly while you do not perceive,"
  39,56,"Lest a soul should say,{1} ",footnotes:1:[On the Day of Resurrection.]
  39,57,"Or [lest] it say, "
  40,34,"And Joseph had already come to you before with clear proofs, but you remained in doubt of that which he brought to you, until when he died, you said, 'Never will Allāh send a messenger after him.' Thus does Allāh leave astray he who is a transgressor and skeptic."
  40,35,"Those who dispute concerning the signs of Allāh without an authority{1} having come to them - great is hatred [of them] in the sight of Allāh and in the sight of those who have believed. Thus does Allāh seal over every heart [belonging to] an arrogant tyrant.",footnotes:1:[i.e., evidence.]
  40,36,"And Pharaoh said, ",footnotes:1:[Means of ascent, pathways.]
  41,13,"But if they turn away, then say, "
  41,14,"[That occurred] when the messengers had come to them before them and after them, [saying], ",footnotes:1:[To send messengers.]
  41,15,"As for ʿAad, they were arrogant upon the earth without right and said, "